#m 0000
menu: Project
In this menu you find all functions concerning the whole project.

#m 0010
menu item: Project » New
The entire flowchart with all refinements will be deleted, so that a new
project can be started.\
The contents of the clipboard are preserved.

#m 0020
submenu: Project » Open
A new flowchart will be opened.\
The currently edited flowchart will be lost. If it has been changed since
the last time you saved it, you will be asked for a confirmation.

#m 0021
menu item: Project » Open » Strux-file...
A flowchart in Strux-format will be loaded.\
The currently edited diagram will be lost. If it has been changed since
the last time you saved it, you will be asked for a confirmation.\
You have to select the flowchart in a filerequester and select "Open" to
load it. If you choose "Cancel", the old diagram is
preserved.\\
The default path of the Strux-files may be set with the menu item "Settings »
Program...". This setting then can be saved.\\
A flowchart in Strux-format
may also be loaded by dragging its icon over the Strux window and
dropping it there.

#m 0022
menu item: Project » Open » Text...
A program will be loaded as source code (in the programming languages "Pascal"
or "C") and converted to a flowchart.\
The currently edited diagram will be lost. If it has been changed since
the last time you saved it, you will be asked for a confirmation.\
You have to select the flowchart in a filerequester and select "Open", after 
that it will be loaded. If you choose "Cancel", the old diagram is
kept.\
Then, you have to indicate the programming language of the source
code.\
The source text will be loaded now and a requester appears, in which all
parts of the program (procedures and functions) are listed. You can select
the part of the program to be loaded. This function can be canceled at
this point, if necessary.\
After selecting "Load", the selected part and all its refinements will be 
converted to a flowchart and displayed.\\
The default path of the Textfiles may be set with the menu item "Settings »
Program...". This setting then can be saved.


#m 0040
menu item: Project » Save
The flowchart is saved in Strux-format. The filename of the last
saving or loading will be used.

#m 0050
submenu: Project » Save As
The currently edited flowchart will be saved to disk. The format
and filename to be used can be chosen in a filerequester.

#m 0051
menu item: Project » Save As » Strux-file...
The flowchart will be saved in Strux-format.\
The filename has to be chosen in a filerequester, the diagram will be saved
after selecting "Save". If you choose "Cancel", the flowchart will not be
saved.\
Whether an icon will be generated or not can be set with the menu item
"Settings » Create Icons ?".\\
The default path of the Strux-files may be set with the menu item "Settings »
Program...". This setting then can be saved.

#m 0052
menu item: Project » Save As » Text...
The flowchart will be saved as text.\
The filename has to be chosen in a filerequester, the diagram will be saved
after selecting "Save". If you choose "Cancel", the flowchart will not be
saved.\
For the translation of the flowchart into text, the previously chosen
translation table is used. It can be selected with the menu item
"Settings » Translation Table...". The text is saved in plain ASCII format.\
If no translation table has been selected yet, you get the
possibility to open one now.\
Whether an icon will be generated or not can be set with the menu item
"Settings » Create Icons ?".\\
The default path of the text files may be set with the menu item "Settings »
Program...". This setting then can be saved.

#m 0053
menu item: Project » Save As » Image...
The flowchart will be saved as an image.\
The filename has to be chosen in a filerequester, the diagram will be saved
after selecting "Save". If you choose "Cancel", the flowchart will not be
saved.\
The image will be saved in the common IFF-ILBM format.\
Whether an icon will be generated or not can be set with the menu item
"Settings » Create Icons ?".\\
The default path of the images may be set with the menu item "Settings »
Program...". This setting can be saved then.

#m 0070
submenu: Project » Print
The flowchart is printed. The settings made with the "Preferences" programs
on the Workbench are used.

#m 0071
menu item: Project » Print » All
The entire diagram (with all refinements) will be printed.\
A window appears where the printing can be stopped.\
The settings made with the "Preferences" programs
on the Workbench are used.

#m 0072
menu item: Project » Print » Displayed
The currently displayed flowchart (without refinements) will be printed.\
A window appears where the printing can be stopped.\
The settings made with the "Preferences" programs
on the Workbench are used.

#m 0073
menu item: Project » Print » Clip
The contents of the clipboard (with all refinements) will be printed.\
A window appears where the printing can be stopped.\
The settings made with the "Preferences" programs
on the Workbench are used.

#m 0090
menu item: Project » About...
Information about the program.\
The requester also displays the name of the public screen on which Strux 
is currently running.

#m 0110
menu item: Project » Quit Strux...
The program will be terminated.\
Before that, a requester appears where
you have to confirm that you really want to quit Strux.\
 If the diagram has been
changed since the last time it was saved, you get the possibility to
save it before you quit. (The diagram is saved in Strux-format)

#m 1000
menu: Edit
This menu contains all functions that are necessary to edit the
flowchart.

#m 1010
menu item: Edit » Cut
If no range is marked, the current block is cut and put to the
clipboard.\
However, if a range has been marked (see menu item "Edit » Mark Range"),
the complete range is cut and put to the clipboard.\
The previous contents of the clipboard are lost !\
All main refinements are cut, these are all the ones which are displayed in
a different color. (see menu item "Refinements » Set Main Refinement")\
After that, the contents of the clipboard can be pasted at any point in
the flowchart (with the menu item "Edit » Paste").\\
The text of the cut blocks can also be inserted into other programs
which support the clipboard. If this is not desired, interference with
other programs can be avoided by setting a different number for the
clipboard unit. This can be done with the menu item "Settings » Program...".

#m 1020
menu item: Edit » Copy
If no range is marked, a copy of the current block is put to the clipboard, 
but it also remains in the flowchart.\
However, if a range has been marked (see menu item "Edit » Mark Range"),
the complete range is copied to the clipboard.\
The previous contents of the clipboard are lost !\
All main refinements are copied, these are the ones which are displayed in
a different color. (see menu item "Refinements » Set Main Refinement")\
After that, the contents of the clipboard can be pasted at any point in
the flowchart (with the menu item "Edit » Paste").\\
The text of the copied blocks can also be inserted into other programs
which support the clipboard. If this is not desired, interference with
other programs can be avoided by setting a different number for the
clipboard unit. This can be done with the menu item "Settings » Program...".

#m 1030
menu item: Edit » Paste
The contents of the clipboard are inserted into the flowchart just after the 
current block.\
The clipboard remains unchanged and its contents can be inserted at
different points.

#m 1040
submenu: Edit » Modify
The properties (text or type) of the current block can be changed.

#m 1041
menu item: Edit » Modify » Text...
The text of the current block can be changed.\
A requester appears showing the text of the block which may be edited.\
After terminating the input with the return key or selecting "Use",
the new text will be written into the block.\
However, when you select "Cancel", the old text remains.

#m 1042
menu item: Edit » Modify » Type...
The type of the current block can be changed.\
A window appears showing a list of all possible types for this block.
If a new type and "Use" is selected, the type of the current block
will be set to the selected one.\
When you select "Cancel", the old type remains.

#m 1060
menu item: Edit » Erase
If no range is marked, the current block is irrevocably erased.\
However, if a range has been marked (see menu item "Edit » Mark Range"),
the complete range is erased.\
All marked main refinements are erased, these are the ones which are 
displayed in a different color. (see menu item "Refinements » Set Main Refinement")\\
You cannot get back what you erase !

#m 1080
menu item: Edit » Mark Range
The current block is taken as the start of a range that may contain several
blocks.\
If the current block is moved down or another block is selected with the
mouse, the marked range grows. A marked range can be cut, copied or
erased with the corresponding items in this menu.\\
Another way of marking a range is to select the first block with the mouse and
moving the mouse to the last block of the range while keeping the
mouse button pressed.\\
While a range is marked, a "M" is displayed in the title bar of the screen.\\
A range can be unmarked by either selecting this menu item again, clicking 
with the mouse on a block above the range or clicking outside the diagram.

#m 1100
menu item: Edit » Open Clip...
A flowchart in Strux-format is loaded into the clipboard.\
The previous contents of the clipboard are lost.\
The file is selected in a filerequester and loaded by selecting "Open".
After that, the contents of the clipboard can be inserted into the flowchart
at any point (see menu item "Edit » Paste").\
When you choose "Cancel", the clipboard is not changed.\\
The default path of the Strux-files may be set with the menu item "Settings »
Program...". This setting then can be saved.

#m 1110
submenu: Edit » Save Clip As
The contents of the clipboard can be saved to disk.

#m 1111
menu item: Edit » Save Clip As » Strux-file...
The contents of the clipboard will be saved in Strux-format.\
The filename has to be chosen in a filerequester, the diagram will be saved
after selecting "Save". If you choose "Cancel", the flowchart will not be
saved.\
Whether an icon will be generated or not can be set with the menu item
"Settings » Create Icons ?".\\
The default path of the Strux-files may be set with the menu item "Settings »
Program...". This setting then can be saved.

#m 1112
menu item: Edit » Save Clip As » Text...
The contents of the clipboard will be saved as text.\
The filename has to be chosen in a filerequester, the diagram will be saved
after selecting "Save". If you choose "Cancel", the flowchart will not be
saved.\
For the translation of the flowchart into text, the previously chosen
translation table is used. It can be selected with the menu item
"Settings » Translation Table...". The text is saved in plain ASCII format.\
If no translation table has been selected yet, you get the
possibility to open one now.\
Whether an icon will be generated or not can be set with the menu item
"Settings » Create Icons ?".\\
The default path of the text files may be set with the menu item "Settings »
Program...". This setting then can be saved.

#m 1113
menu item: Edit » Save Clip As » Image...
The contents of the clipboard will be saved as an image.\
The filename has to be chosen in a filerequester, the diagram will be saved
after selecting "Save". If you choose "Cancel", the flowchart will not be
saved.\
The image will be saved in the common IFF-ILBM format.\
Whether an icon will be generated or not can be set with the menu item
"Settings » Create Icons ?".\\
The default path of the images may be set with the menu item "Settings »
Program...". This setting then can be saved.


#m 2000
menu: Refinements
Here you find all functions concerning the refinement of blocks. With
a refinement, the function of a block can be specified more precisely
with an additional flowchart.

#m 2010
menu item: Refinements » Refine Block
A refinement is attached to the current block, this means that the function
of this block is described more precisely in a seperate flowchart.\
A new flowchart appears on the screen with the name of the refined block
as the title. You can edit this flowchart with all the known functions
including further refinements.\
A refined block is shown in bold letters if the menu option "Refinements »
Show ?" is selected.\
If a block already has a refinement, you can get into its refinement with a
double click on the block.\\
With the menu item "Refinements » Higher Level" you can get back to the
block that has been refined.

#m 2020
menu item: Refinements » Higher Level
You get back to the previous level of refinements, exactly to the block
which has been refined.\\
By double clicking on the top border of the diagram (not the window)
you also get back to the higher level.

#m 2030
menu item: Refinements » Top Level
You immediately get back to the top level of the flowchart.

#m 2050
menu item: Refinements » Show ?
Here you can select whether all refined blocks should be marked or not.\
All refined blocks are shown in bold letters. One of them is written in
another color, which means that the refinement is actually attached
to this block. All operations done with this block (Cut, Copy, Paste etc.)
have influence on the refinement.

#m 2060
submenu: Refinements » to "Subroutine"
You can choose if refinements are shown as blocks of type "Subroutine".\
This can be useful as blocks of type "Subroutine" are translated differently
(e.g. as a procedure call) when saving the flowchart as text.

#m 2061
menu item: Refinements » to "Subroutine" » Automatically ?
When this menu item is switched on, each block that is refined is converted
to the type "Subroutine".\
This can be useful as blocks of type "Subroutine" are translated differently
(e.g. as a procedure call) when saving the flowchart as text.\
However, the conversion is only possible with blocks of type "Action",
"Input" or "Output". All other blocks keep their type.

#m 2062
menu item: Refinements » to "Subroutine" » Change All
All refined blocks are converted to the type "Subroutine".\
This can be useful as blocks of type "Subroutine" are translated differently
(e.g. as a procedure call) when saving the flowchart as text.\
However, the conversion is only possible with blocks of type "Action",
"Input" or "Output". All other blocks keep their type.\\
ATTENTION: The conversion cannot be reversed !

#m 2070
menu item: Refinements » Set Main Refinement
If the current block has a refinement, the actual flowchart of this 
refinement will be attached to this block. Its text will be shown with a
different color if the menu item "Refinements » Show ?" is switched on.\
All operations done with this block (Cut, Copy, Paste etc.) now have 
influence on the refinement.



#m 3000
menu: Add
When selecting an item from this menu, a new block is created and inserted
into the flowchart. A new block is always inserted below the current block.

#m 3010
menu item: Add » Action
A simple action will be inserted below the current block.\
(imperative construct)

#m 3030
menu item: Add » If Then
A simple decision will inserted below the current block. The "else" part
can be added later.\
(monadic selective)

#m 3040
menu item: Add » If Then Else
A decision where one of two branches is taken will be inserted below the current
block.\
(dyadic selective)

#m 3050
menu item: Add » Select of
A decision with a choice of several branches will be inserted below the
current block.\
(multiple exclusive selective)

#m 3060
menu item: Add » Case
Another branch with another condition will be added to a "Select" block.

#m 3070
menu item: Add » Default/Else
A "Default" branch will be added to a "Select" block\
or\
an "Else" branch will be added to an "If" block.

#m 3090
menu item: Add » While
A loop will be inserted below the current block.\
(pre-tested iteration)

#m 3100
menu item: Add » Repeat Until
A loop will be inserted below the current block.\
(post-tested iteration)

#m 3110
menu item: Add » For ... Repeat
A count loop will be inserted below the current block.

#m 3120
menu item: Add » Repeat Forever
An endless loop will be inserted below the current block.

#m 3130
menu item: Add » Exit
A command to exit a loop will be inserted below the current block.\
(termination)

#m 3150
menu item: Add » Subroutine
A subroutine call will be inserted below the current block.

#m 3160
menu item: Add » Program
The title of the program or a connection to other flowcharts will be 
inserted below the current block.\
(terminator, connector)

#m 3170
menu item: Add » Input
An input will be inserted below the current block.\
(manual operation)\
The graphical representation is the same as for the type "Output", but both
types are translated differently when saving the flowchart as text.

#m 3180
menu item: Add » Output
An output will be inserted below the current block.\
(manual operation)\
The graphical representation is the same as for the type "Input", but both
types are translated differently when saving the flowchart as text.

#m 3190
menu item: Add » Parallel
A parallel processing of several branches (processes) will be inserted below 
the current block.\
(parallel construct)

#m 3200
menu item: Add » Process
Another branch will be added to a parallel construct.


#m 4000
menu: Settings
Here you can make all settings for Strux.

#m 4010
menu item: Settings » Diagram...
A requester appears where all settings concerning the 
rendering of the diagram can be made.\
These are:\
· The representation of the flowchart (normal flowchart, Nassi-Shneiderman
flowchart or Pseudocode)\
· The font for each type of representation\\
You can get more information by pressing the help key while the requester
is displayed.

#m 4020
menu item: Settings » Screen...
A requester appears where you can choose the screen on which the
Strux window is displayed.\
It is possible to choose an already opened public screen or open an own
screen.\\
You can get more information by pressing the help key while the requester
is displayed.

#m 4030
menu item: Settings » Program...
A requester appears where you can make all settings concerning the user
interface.\
These are:\
· The paths for Strux, text and image files\
· Switches in the menus "Refinements" and "Settings"\
· The number of the clipboard\\
You can get more information by pressing the help key while the requester
is displayed.

#m 4050
menu item: Settings » Translation Table...
A requester appears where you can edit a translation table that is used
when saving the flowchart as text. You can define the translation of all
block types.\
A translation table can also be opened or saved with this requester.\
You can get more information by pressing the help key while the requester
is displayed.

#m 4070
menu item: Settings » Create Icons ?
You can select if an icon should be created or not for a saved flowchart 
of type Strux-file, text or image.

#m 4080
menu item: Settings » Workbench ?
You can select if the Workbench screen should stay open.\
If this item is selected (the checkmark appears), the program tries to open
the Workbench screen (if it is not already open). Otherwise it tries to
close the Workbench screen.\
If the program does not succeed in closing the screen (e.g. because other
programs opened their windows there), a requester appears reporting the
failure.

#m 4100
menu item: Settings » Open Settings...
Open a previouly saved setting and use it.\
A filerequester appears where you can select a settings file. Only files
with the ending ".prefs" are shown, so you can easily find settings files.\
The selected settings are loaded and the program will change all settings
to the new ones.\\
When starting Strux, the settings are read from the file "Strux.prefs".
By opening this settings file, you get back your starting settings.

#m 4110
menu item: Settings » Save Settings
All settings are saved to disk. The name of the last settings file
you loaded is used. After starting Strux, this is the name 
"Strux.prefs".\
The settings contain the selections made in the top four items of this
menu and the position and size of the Strux main window.\\
When starting Strux, the settings are read from the file "Strux.prefs".

#m 4120
menu item: Settings » Save Settings As...
All settings are saved to disk.\
A filerequester appears where you can select the name of your settings
to be saved. The name should end with ".prefs" in order to find the settings 
easily.\
When starting Strux, the settings are read from the file "Strux.prefs".
So, if you save your settings with this name, Strux will start the next 
time with exactly these settings.



#w 00
Strux
In the main window, the flowchart is displayed. The graphical representation
can be chosen with the menu item "Settings » Diagram". You can move the
visible part with the scrollbars in the window borders.\
The current block is shown in reversed colors.\
Selecting the close gadget has the same meaning as the menu item
"Project » Quit Strux...".
#

#w 01
window: Change type
You can change the type of the current block.\
A list with all possible types for the current block is shown. If you
choose a type from the list and select "Use", the type of the current
block is changed to the chosen type.\
By selecting "Cancel" or the close gadget the type will not be changed.

#w 02
window: text input
When this window appears, you can immediatly type in your text.\
After the text input has been finished by pressing the return key or
selecting the "Use" button, the text will be used for the block.\
By selecting "Cancel" or the close gadget the old text remains.\
If no text is typed in although one is expected in the flowchart,
"???" will be taken as the text for the block. If you really want no
text to appear, enter a space character.

#w 03
window: Diagram Preferences
You can make all Settings concerning the rendering of your flowchart.\\
Show As:\
Here you can select the representation of the diagram.\
· Nassi-Shneiderman:\
graphical representation according to Nassi-Shneiderman\
· Flowchart:\
the common graphical representation of a flowchart\
· Pseudocode:\
textual representation in a pseudo-language, where the different types
are described by keywords and the structure by indents.\\
Font:\
The selected font for each of the three representations is shown. By
clicking on the corresponding "select..." button, you can choose the 
font in a fontrequester.\\
Meaning of the three buttons "Save", "Use" and "Cancel":\
· "Save": The settings made in this window are saved and used.\
· "Use": The settings are used but not saved. They will be lost when you
quit Strux.\
· "Cancel": The old settings are preserved, no change is carried out.\
The close gadget has the same meaning as the "Cancel" button.

#w 04
window: Screen Preferences
You can define the screen on which you want to work with Strux.\
In the upper part of the window, a list of all currently opened public
screens is shown. Here you can choose any screen.\\
When selecting "Own Screen", Strux will open an own public screen and
open its window there. The name of the screen is displayed when you select
the menu item "Project » About...". The appearance of the screen can be
defined by the buttons "Display Mode...", "Font..." and "Palette...".\\
· "Display Mode...": A screenmode requester appears.\
· "Font...": You can select the font for your screen in a fontrequester.
All menus and windows appear with this font.\
· "Palette...": The colors of the screen can be defined. This is only
possible when Strux is already running on an own screen.\\
Meaning of the three buttons "Save", "Use" and "Cancel":\
· "Save": The settings made in this window are saved and used.\
· "Use": The settings are used but not saved. They will be lost when you
quit Strux.\
· "Cancel": The old settings are preserved, no change is carried out.\
The close gadget has the same meaning as the "Cancel" button.

#w 05
window: Program Preferences
· Paths:\
The default paths used for saving and opening Strux-files, texts or
images are shown. They can be changed by clicking on the appropriate 
"select..." buttons.\\
· Refinements:\
The states of the checkmarks for the items "Show ?" and "to Subroutine » 
automatically ?" in the "Refinements" menu can be set.\\
· Other:\
The states of the checkmarks for the items "Workbench ?" and "Create Icons ?"
in the "Settings" menu can be set.\
· Clipboard unit:\
The number of the clipboard unit used for cut, copy and paste operations
can be set here. Normally all programs use unit zero, so they can exchange
data. If you do not want this, you can change the number.\\
Meaning of the three buttons "Save", "Use" and "Cancel":\
· "Save": The settings made in this window are saved and used.\
· "Use": The settings are used but not saved. They will be lost when you
quit Strux.\
· "Cancel": The old settings are preserved, no change is carried out.\
The close gadget has the same meaning as the "Cancel" button.

#w 06
window: Screen Display Mode
The format of the Strux screen can be defined here.\
In the upper part of the window there is a list of all available display
modes. You can select any mode from this list.\
The width and height of the screen can be chosen freely as long as the
width is greater than 640 and height is greater than 200 Pixels.\
If the "Default" gadget is selected, the standard size of the selected
display mode will be taken.\
With the gadget "AutoScroll" you can select if the visible size of the
screen scrolls automatically when you reach the border.\\
"OK" confirms the selection while "Cancel" or the close gadget preserves
the old settings and does not change anything.

#w 07
window: Screen Palette
Adjust color for own screen.\
In the upper part of the requester you can choose the color to be changed.
With the sliders you can adjust the red, green and blue portion of the
selected color. The effect is immediately visible.\
By selecting the button "Workbench colors", the color settings from
the Workbench are taken.\\
"OK" confirms the selection while "Cancel" or the close gadget preserves
the old colors and does not change anything.

#w 08
window: Translation Table
Edit a translation table that is used when saving the flowchart as text.\
In the upper part of the window, the name of the currently used 
translation table is displayed.\
Below, there is a list showing the translation of each type of block.
After clicking on an item, you can edit it in the string gadget below
the list.\\
There are several control codes:\
· %n : start new line\
· %t : text of the block\
· %bn: attached program branch, n means the amount of characters by which
the block is indented\
· %v : (only possible in "Main Part" and "Refinements") local refinements\\
You can further select if space characters are put out as an underline
character. This is useful with names that consists of more than one
word. When selecting "Only in Refinem.", the space characters are only
converted to underline characters in names of refinements.\\
With "Open..." and "Save As..." you can open or save translation tables
to disk, by selecting "New" you can generate an empty table.\
"Save" saved the table with the same name it was loaded by and closes
the window.\
By selecting "Use", the new table is used but not saved.\
"Cancel" restores the old table.

#w 10
window: Load Sourcecode
In the list there are shown all procedures and functions found in the
sourcecode. The top entry is the main part if there is one in the
sourcecode. In "C" it is always called "main", in Pascal it is the
name which is found in the text. (e.g. the name of "PROGRAM title
(INPUT, OUTPUT); ..." is "title")\
You can choose the part of the program which should be converted into
a flowchart. All refinements (procedures, functions) are converted,
too.\
"Load" converts the chosen part.\
"Cancel" breaks the loading.


#w 11
window: Help  (this window)
All help texts are displayed in this window.\
With the scroll bar and the arrows on the right side you can roll the
text.\\
There is help available for all menus and menu items, all windows and
some special terms.\
To get help, do the following:\\
· menus and menu items:\
Select the menu or menu item as usual with the right mouse button, but
keep the button pressed. Then, while still holding the right mouse button,
press the help key. After a short time, the help text will be displayed
in this window.\\
· windows:\
Activate the window you need help for by clicking into that window.
Then press the help key. A help text appears for that window.\\
· special terms:\
Select the button "Keywords" in the bottom of this window. A list of
words for which there are help texts appears. By clicking on a word
the help is displayed.\\
When the help is not needed any longer, you can close the window with
the close gadget. It is also possible to continue work while the help
window is displayed.\\
The help texts are for a quick reference and assume that you have
some basic knowledge about Strux. You can find more information and
an introduction to Strux in your printed manual.

